#: /tmp/cicero-EpGA/ref/set_transaction.xml:49(title) 
msgid "Description"
msgstr ""

#: /tmp/cicero-EpGA/ref/set_transaction.xml:51(para) 
msgid "The <command>SET TRANSACTION</command> command sets the characteristics of the current transaction. It has no effect on any subsequent transactions. <command>SET SESSION CHARACTERISTICS</command> sets the default transaction characteristics for subsequent transactions of a session. These defaults can be overridden by <command>SET TRANSACTION</command> for an individual transaction."
msgstr ""

#: /tmp/cicero-EpGA/ref/set_transaction.xml:61(para) 
msgid "The available transaction characteristics are the transaction isolation level, the transaction access mode (read/write or read-only), and the deferrable mode."
msgstr ""

#: /tmp/cicero-EpGA/ref/set_transaction.xml:73(literal) 
msgid "READ COMMITTED"
msgstr ""

#: /tmp/cicero-EpGA/ref/set_transaction.xml:75(para) 
msgid "A statement can only see rows committed before it began. This is the default."
msgstr ""

#: /tmp/cicero-EpGA/ref/set_transaction.xml:83(literal) 
msgid "REPEATABLE READ"
msgstr ""

#: /tmp/cicero-EpGA/ref/set_transaction.xml:85(para) 
msgid "All statements of the current transaction can only see rows committed before the first query or data-modification statement was executed in this transaction."
msgstr ""

#: /tmp/cicero-EpGA/ref/set_transaction.xml:94(literal) 
msgid "SERIALIZABLE"
msgstr ""

#: /tmp/cicero-EpGA/ref/set_transaction.xml:96(para) 
msgid "All statements of the current transaction can only see rows committed before the first query or data-modification statement was executed in this transaction. If a pattern of reads and writes among concurrent serializable transactions would create a situation which could not have occurred for any serial (one-at-a-time) execution of those transactions, one of them will be rolled back with a <literal>serialization_failure</literal><literal>SQLSTATE</literal>."
msgstr ""

#: /tmp/cicero-EpGA/ref/set_transaction.xml:67(para) 
msgid "The isolation level of a transaction determines what data the transaction can see when other transactions are running concurrently: <placeholder-1/> The SQL standard defines one additional level, <literal>READ UNCOMMITTED</literal>. In <productname>PostgreSQL</productname><literal>READ UNCOMMITTED</literal> is treated as <literal>READ COMMITTED</literal>."
msgstr ""

#: /tmp/cicero-EpGA/ref/set_transaction.xml:115(para) 
msgid "The transaction isolation level cannot be changed after the first query or data-modification statement (<command>SELECT</command>, <command>INSERT</command>, <command>DELETE</command>, <command>UPDATE</command>, <command>FETCH</command>, or <command>COPY</command>) of a transaction has been executed. See <xref linkend=\"mvcc\"/> for more information about transaction isolation and concurrency control."
msgstr ""

#: /tmp/cicero-EpGA/ref/set_transaction.xml:125(para) 
msgid "The transaction access mode determines whether the transaction is read/write or read-only. Read/write is the default. When a transaction is read-only, the following SQL commands are disallowed: <literal>INSERT</literal>, <literal>UPDATE</literal>, <literal>DELETE</literal>, and <literal>COPY FROM</literal> if the table they would write to is not a temporary table; all <literal>CREATE</literal>, <literal>ALTER</literal>, and <literal>DROP</literal> commands; <literal>COMMENT</literal>, <literal>GRANT</literal>, <literal>REVOKE</literal>, <literal>TRUNCATE</literal>; and <literal>EXPLAIN ANALYZE</literal> and <literal>EXECUTE</literal> if the command they would execute is among those listed. This is a high-level notion of read-only that does not prevent all writes to disk."
msgstr ""

#: /tmp/cicero-EpGA/ref/set_transaction.xml:141(para) 
msgid "The <literal>DEFERRABLE</literal> transaction property has no effect unless the transaction is also <literal>SERIALIZABLE</literal> and <literal>READ ONLY</literal>. When all of these properties are set on a transaction, the transaction may block when first acquiring its snapshot, after which it is able to run without the normal overhead of a <literal>SERIALIZABLE</literal> transaction and without any risk of contributing to or being canceled by a serialization failure. This mode is well suited for long-running reports or backups."
msgstr ""

#: /tmp/cicero-EpGA/ref/set_transaction.xml:154(title) 
msgid "Notes"
msgstr ""

#: /tmp/cicero-EpGA/ref/set_transaction.xml:156(para) 
msgid "If <command>SET TRANSACTION</command> is executed without a prior <command>START TRANSACTION</command> or <command>BEGIN</command>, it will appear to have no effect, since the transaction will immediately end."
msgstr ""

#: /tmp/cicero-EpGA/ref/set_transaction.xml:163(para) 
msgid "It is possible to dispense with <command>SET TRANSACTION</command> by instead specifying the desired <replaceable class=\"parameter\">transaction_modes</replaceable> in <command>BEGIN</command> or <command>START TRANSACTION</command>."
msgstr ""

#: /tmp/cicero-EpGA/ref/set_transaction.xml:170(para) 
msgid "The session default transaction modes can also be set by setting the configuration parameters <xref linkend=\"guc-default-transaction-isolation\"/>, <xref linkend=\"guc-default-transaction-read-only\"/>, and <xref linkend=\"guc-default-transaction-deferrable\"/>. (In fact <command>SET SESSION CHARACTERISTICS</command> is just a verbose equivalent for setting these variables with <command>SET</command>.) This means the defaults can be set in the configuration file, via <command>ALTER DATABASE</command>, etc. Consult <xref linkend=\"runtime-config\"/> for more information."
msgstr ""

#: /tmp/cicero-EpGA/ref/set_transaction.xml:184(title) 
msgid "Compatibility"
msgstr ""

#: /tmp/cicero-EpGA/ref/set_transaction.xml:186(para) 
msgid "Both commands are defined in the <acronym>SQL</acronym> standard. <literal>SERIALIZABLE</literal> is the default transaction isolation level in the standard. In <productname>PostgreSQL</productname> the default is ordinarily <literal>READ COMMITTED</literal>, but you can change it as mentioned above."
msgstr ""

#: /tmp/cicero-EpGA/ref/set_transaction.xml:195(para) 
msgid "In the SQL standard, there is one other transaction characteristic that can be set with these commands: the size of the diagnostics area. This concept is specific to embedded SQL, and therefore is not implemented in the <productname>PostgreSQL</productname> server."
msgstr ""

#: /tmp/cicero-EpGA/ref/set_transaction.xml:202(para) 
msgid "The <literal>DEFERRABLE</literal><replaceable class=\"parameter\">transaction_mode</replaceable> is a <productname>PostgreSQL</productname> language extension."
msgstr ""

#: /tmp/cicero-EpGA/ref/set_transaction.xml:208(para) 
msgid "The SQL standard requires commas between successive <replaceable class=\"parameter\">transaction_modes</replaceable>, but for historical reasons <productname>PostgreSQL</productname> allows the commas to be omitted."
msgstr ""

